overview:
Matheau J. W. Stout, Esq. is a Maryland entrepreneur lawyer representing business owners and their companies in all legal matters from start up to acquisition.

Matt Stout’s entrepreneur law practice focuses on providing on call general legal counsel to business owners in the areas of corporate law, technology licensing, start up planning, mergers and acquisitions, succession planning, estate planning for business owners, securities law, contracts and business tax compliance.

Matt Stout does not bill hourly. Instead, the business owner clients of Matheau J. W. Stout, Esq. receive detailed proposals before cases begin in which all work is itemized, and bundled under value based flat fees.

This unique element of Matt Stout’s entrepreneur law practice provides entrepreneurs, company founders, CEOs, and business owners with the certainty and confidence necessary to move forward in complicated transactions since they do not have to worry about the “meter running” or being surprised with a large hourly bill.
